[
    {
        "text": "In 1838, Georgetown\nUniversity",
        "start": 0.625,
        "duration": 2.305
    },
    {
        "text": "sold 272 people to Louisiana\nto save the university",
        "start": 2.93,
        "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
        "text": "from bankruptcy.",
        "start": 6.81,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Among those that were\nsold were my ancestors.",
        "start": 8.13,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "That university would not\nbe here today had it not been",
        "start": 11.64,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "for my grandparents.",
        "start": 15.18,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "That was a long time ago,\nbut the effects of that",
        "start": 17.22,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "are still felt today.",
        "start": 19.92,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "There are disproportionate\nnegative outcomes",
        "start": 21.21,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "for those who are descendants\nof slaves that can only",
        "start": 23.34,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "be explained by the fact that\nthis enslavement happened,",
        "start": 25.65,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "reparation didn't happen,\nand now is the time.",
        "start": 28.65,
        "duration": 3.479
    },
    {
        "text": "In October,\nGeorgetown University",
        "start": 32.129,
        "duration": 2.131
    },
    {
        "text": "announced that they would\nraise $400,000 a year",
        "start": 34.26,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "for the descendants of\nthe 272 enslaved Americans",
        "start": 37.17,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "that were sold to Louisiana.",
        "start": 40.49,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "They said this money\nwill be spent beginning",
        "start": 42.39,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "in the fall of 2020.",
        "start": 44.31,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "My family might\nbe making history",
        "start": 46.77,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "in the United States.",
        "start": 49.35,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "I might become\none of the first",
        "start": 50.73,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "in the history of America\nto receive reparations.",
        "start": 53.34,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "Mechanicville\nis the area that",
        "start": 61.62,
        "duration": 3.21
    },
    {
        "text": "is heavily populated with\nGeorgetown descendants,",
        "start": 64.83,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "including myself\nwhere I grew up.",
        "start": 68.43,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "And Mechanicville\nis less than a half",
        "start": 71.4,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "a mile away from where\nthe plantations were where",
        "start": 74.31,
        "duration": 4.5
    },
    {
        "text": "our ancestors were enslaved.",
        "start": 78.81,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, you had people\non very low income.",
        "start": 81.42,
        "duration": 3.4
    },
    {
        "text": "Sometimes, they didn't\nhave any income.",
        "start": 84.82,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "Some of us have done well\nif we were able to get out",
        "start": 87.24,
        "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
        "text": "and get an education,\nand a lot of us haven't.",
        "start": 91.14,
        "duration": 4.44
    },
    {
        "text": "And they could really use\nsome assistance or help.",
        "start": 95.58,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "Mom?",
        "start": 103.407,
        "duration": 0.724
    },
    {
        "text": "Hm?",
        "start": 104.131,
        "duration": 0.729
    },
    {
        "text": "We might be the first\nthat receive some form",
        "start": 104.86,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "of reparations for slavery.",
        "start": 107.62,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "It may start with you.",
        "start": 110.26,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, I think it would\nbe a wonderful thing.",
        "start": 111.78,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Start out with me and then\ncontinue on with everybody",
        "start": 114.76,
        "duration": 7.67
    },
    {
        "text": "who would be in need.",
        "start": 122.43,
        "duration": 2.696
    },
    {
        "text": "There is so much I missed\nout on, but from the goodness",
        "start": 125.126,
        "duration": 4.263
    },
    {
        "text": "of God, I'm still here.",
        "start": 129.389,
        "duration": 2.811
    },
    {
        "text": "My mom — I will never\nforget — had one dress.",
        "start": 132.2,
        "duration": 6.25
    },
    {
        "text": "She'd wash that\ndress out at night",
        "start": 138.45,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "and hang it on the\nback of her chair",
        "start": 141.45,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "to the fireplace\nto dry to have",
        "start": 143.05,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "it to put on the next day.",
        "start": 145.95,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "And my mom — patches\non top of patches.",
        "start": 148.1,
        "duration": 3.755
    },
    {
        "text": "So what do you think that —",
        "start": 156.84,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "just maybe one\nthing you think",
        "start": 158.71,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "that Georgetown should do?",
        "start": 160.29,
        "duration": 2.81
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, my house could be\nupgraded, for one thing.",
        "start": 163.1,
        "duration": 3.94
    },
    {
        "text": "In my community\nwhere I grew up,",
        "start": 167.04,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "reparations would\ndefinitely help.",
        "start": 169.2,
        "duration": 3.06
    },
    {
        "text": "If I was given reparations,\nI would definitely",
        "start": 172.26,
        "duration": 3.81
    },
    {
        "text": "set some of that money\naside for my son's future.",
        "start": 176.07,
        "duration": 4.05
    },
    {
        "text": "My first thing is\nto get something",
        "start": 180.12,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "for the elderly people.",
        "start": 183.6,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "I would feel\nthat my ancestors",
        "start": 185.28,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "are rejoicing in heaven.",
        "start": 187.68,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": "It's $400,000.",
        "start": 190.03,
        "duration": 2.51
    },
    {
        "text": "For each family?",
        "start": 192.54,
        "duration": 0.92
    },
    {
        "text": "No.",
        "start": 193.46,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[CHUCKLING]",
        "start": 193.96,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "It's just $400,000\nfor over 7,000 people.",
        "start": 196.07,
        "duration": 5.17
    },
    {
        "text": "Oh my.",
        "start": 201.24,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "Not much.",
        "start": 202.77,
        "duration": 2.77
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you think $400,000\ncomes close to what",
        "start": 205.54,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "we need as a people?",
        "start": 207.81,
        "duration": 2.285
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's $400,000.",
        "start": 210.095,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes.",
        "start": 210.845,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "O.K., so the descendants\nthat's living now—",
        "start": 212.485,
        "duration": 4.385
    },
    {
        "text": "you put that at how\nmany, about 8,000?",
        "start": 216.87,
        "duration": 1.659
    },
    {
        "text": "There's about 8,000.",
        "start": 218.529,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": "There's probably more.",
        "start": 219.404,
        "duration": 1.696
    },
    {
        "text": "Equal $50.",
        "start": 221.1,
        "duration": 4.07
    },
    {
        "text": "$50.",
        "start": 225.17,
        "duration": 1.818
    },
    {
        "text": "It's a slap in the face.",
        "start": 226.988,
        "duration": 1.292
    },
    {
        "text": "Not just a slap in the face,\nthat's a kick in the behind",
        "start": 228.28,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "also.",
        "start": 230.62,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "Georgetown University\nis currently",
        "start": 231.97,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "deciding how this\nmoney will be spent,",
        "start": 233.89,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "but said it will go towards\nprojects that support",
        "start": 236.41,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "descendant communities.",
        "start": 238.87,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "I think Georgetown has\nsuch an opportunity here",
        "start": 241.0,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "to take the lead on this.",
        "start": 243.58,
        "duration": 1.495
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't think they\nshould go bankrupt,",
        "start": 245.075,
        "duration": 1.625
    },
    {
        "text": "but $400,000 is not\ngoing to do it.",
        "start": 246.7,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Someone in authority\nat Georgetown",
        "start": 249.34,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "needs to come\ndown and actually",
        "start": 251.95,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "meet with each\ndescendant and see",
        "start": 253.36,
        "duration": 2.669
    },
    {
        "text": "what each descendant needs.",
        "start": 256.029,
        "duration": 1.981
    },
    {
        "text": "We don't need to make\nwhite people wrong.",
        "start": 258.01,
        "duration": 2.069
    },
    {
        "text": "We don't need to make\nGeorgetown wrong.",
        "start": 260.079,
        "duration": 2.551
    },
    {
        "text": "We need to ask\nourselves, what do",
        "start": 262.63,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "we need to do to ensure\nthat all of Americans",
        "start": 264.76,
        "duration": 3.78
    },
    {
        "text": "have full access\nto every right",
        "start": 268.54,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "that it means to\nbe an American?",
        "start": 271.3,
        "duration": 2.9
    }
]